owl:Ontology.terms:description: This ontology extends the SAREF ontology for the automotive domain. This work has been developed in the context of the STF 566, which was established with the goal to create four SAREF extensions, one of them for the automotive domain.
owl:Ontology.terms:title: SAREF extension for automotive

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A spatial representation for a given feature.

The relation between something and the point, or other geometrical thing in space, where it is. For example, the realtionship between a radio tower and a Point with a given lat and long. Or a relationship between a park and its outline as a closed arc of points, or a road and its location as a arc (a sequence of points). Clearly in practice there will be limit to the accuracy of any such statement, but one would expect an accuracy appropriate for the size of the object and uses such as mapping .
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: location

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Beginning of a temporal entity
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasBeginning

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: End of a temporal entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasEnd

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship indicating a composite entity that consists of other entities (e.g., a temperature/humidity sensor that consists of a temperature sensor and a humidity sensor)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: consists of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship specifying the property that can be controlled by a certain device
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: controls property

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship between a feature of interest and a property of that feature
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: controls property

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship specifying the devices that can control a certain property
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is controlled by device

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship specifying the devices that can measure a certain property
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is measured by device

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship identifying the unit of measure used for a certain entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is measured in

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between a device and the measurements it makes. Such measurement will link together the value of the measurement, its unit of measure and the property to which it relates.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: makes measurement

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between a measurement and the device that made it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: measurementMadeBy

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship specifying the property that can be measured by a certain device
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: measures property

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship between a property and the measurements it relates to
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: relates to measurement

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship between a measurement and the property it relates to
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: relates to property

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: File format to storage the data
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasFormat

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Exists a relation between classes
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is related to

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to describe the entities that can compose the vehicle environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: consists Of Entity

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to describe the type of equipment that can compose the vehicle environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: consists of equipment

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to describe the events that can compose the vehicle environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: consists of event

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to describe the objects that can compose the vehicle environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: consists of object

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to describe the users that can compose the vehicle environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: consists of user

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to decribe the vehicles that can compose the vehicle environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: consists of vehicle

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship specifying the position (absolute or relative position) that can be detected by a certain device
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: detects position

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between an entity, e.g., a vehicle or road entity, and AbsolutePosition to represent its absolute position
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasAbsolutePosition

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to define the level of automation of a singular vehicle. According to SAE J3016, there are five levels of automation: - Level 0: No Driving Automation. - Level 1: Driver assistance. - Level 2: Partial driving automation. - Level 3: Conditional driving automation. - Level 4: High driving automation. - Level 5: Full Driving automation. .
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasAutomationLevel

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express that the vehicle has the capacity to reduce its speed (by action on the brake pedal or an autonomous actuator)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasBrakeCapacity

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between an estimated measurement (saref:Measurement class) and its confidence (s4auto:Confidence)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasConfidence

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation that allows to specify the unit of measure associated with a certain confidence
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has confidence unit of measure

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation that defines the destination of an automotive object. For example, in a platoon, the current platoon leader defines the platoon destination. Following vehicles will share (partially) the route of the leader and can, therefore, have different final destinations.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasDestination

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the destination of a vehicle in terms of an Address
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasDestinationAddress

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the destination of a vehicle, a platoon or a route in terms of an end point with latitude and longitude
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasDestinationEndPoint

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation that allows to describe the environment of a vehicle
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasEnvironment

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express that, during the forming state, a vehicle member of a platoon is given an estimated rendezvous location for joining the platoon. It is expressed in global coordinates (lat, long, alt), e.g. according to WGS 84.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasEstimatedRendezvousLocation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the height of an entity, e.g., a vehicle or an entity in the vehicle environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasHeight

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between an entity and its identifier (s4auto:Identifier) which is used to identify 1) a vehicle (station) during data exchange with other devices/stations 2) a platoon during data exchange with other devices/stations, 3) a parking spot within a parking area during data exchange with other devices/stations. In all cases, this identifier may be a pseudonym. It may change over space and/or over time.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasIdentifier

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the length of an entity, e.g., a vehicle or an entity in the vehicle environment or a platoon (Length of the platoon is the sum of all vehicles' length + inter-vehicle distance)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasLength

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A general relationship to express that an entity can have members
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasMember

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the movement of an entity in the vehicle environment.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasMovement

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the opening time of parking spot
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasOpeningTimeAvailability

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the origin of an entity (e.g., a vehicle or a route) in terms of a StartPoint
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasOrigin

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the state of a parking spot
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasParkingSpotState

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the state of a vehicle that is parking
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasParkingVehicleState

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the state of a vehicle related to its environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasPerceptionState

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express that a platoon can have vehicles as its members
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasPlatoonMember

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relatiA relation to express that a vehicle member of a platoon has a platoon position that is defined as the index of the vehicle in the platoon starting from zero (leader) up to N (trailing vehicle)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasPlatoonPosition

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to specify that in a platoon a vehicle can assume roles such as: unknown, leader, follower, ready-for-leading, trailing, etc.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasPlatoonRole

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the state of a platoon
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasPlatoonState

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the state of a vehicle in a platoon
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasPlatoonVehicleState

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to define the position of an entity
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has position

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between an entity, e.g., a vehicle or road entity, and RelativePosition to represent its relative position (e.g., a car is x,y,z in front of another car)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasPlatoonPosition

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between Vehicle and RoadTopologyPosition to represent the road topology position of a vehicle
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasRoadTopologyPosition

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A general relation to express that an entity can have a role
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasRole

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the route of an entity, e.g., a vehicle or a platoon
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasRoute

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the shape of an entity in the vehicle environment.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasShape

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express that a platoon has a size. This size is defined as 1) the total number of vehicles currently in the platoon; or 2) Length of the platoon (sum of all vehicles' length + inter-vehicle distance) via s4auto:hasLength property
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasSize

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An hasState relation to connect to a certain state. The saref:hasState property could not be reused because it has domain saref:Device, but a s4auto:Platoon or s4auto:Vehicle are not devices. Therefore, a new s4auto:hasState property with subroperties has been created.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasState

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express that a vehicle can have members in its environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasVehicleEnvironmentMember

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between Vehicle and VehicleRole classes, to express the role the vehicle plays in traffic. If not specified, it is assumed that it takes a default value. Otherwise, possible values to be specified are: publicTransport, specialTransport, dangerousGoods, roadWork, rescue, emergency, safetyCar, agriculture, commercial, military, roadOperator, taxi (see ETSI TR 103 508).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasVehicleRole

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the width of an entity, e.g., a vehicle or an entity in the vehicle environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasWidth

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the intermediate destination of a route (e.g., of a vehicle or a platoon) in terms of RoutePoint
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isCollectionOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between the confidence (s4auto:Confidence class) of an estimated measurement and this measurement (saref:Measurement class)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isConfidenceOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A general relationship to express that an entity is a member of another entity
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isMemberOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express that a vehicle can be member of a platoon
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isMemberOfPlatoon

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express that an entity, e.g., a vehicle, can be member of another vehicle's environment
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isMemberOfVehicleEnvironment

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express that a device can use different types of measurements, such as speed, position of detected road objects (e.g., bicycles, vehicles). This applies in particular to the ElectronicControlUnit and TrafficLightController classes.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: usesMeasurement

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: In SAREF4AUTO, a relation to express that the vehicle has a subsystem called ‘ElectronicControlUnit' (ECU) that provides measurements about relevant properties, such as speed, acceleration, position, etc.
Links a system to one of its sub systems
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasSubSystem

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: In SAREF4AUTO, a relation to express that the the ElectronicControlUnit (ECU) is a subsystem of the vehicle.

Links a system to its super system. Properties of subsystems somehow contribute to the properties of the super system. The exact meaning of "contribute is defined by sub properties of s4syst:subSystemOf. Property s4syst:subSystemOf is transitive.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: subSystemOf

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The WGS84 altitude of a SpatialThing (decimal meters above the local reference ellipsoid).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: altitude

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The WGS84 latitude of a SpatialThing (decimal degrees).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: latitude

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The WGS84 longitude of a SpatialThing (decimal degrees).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: longitude

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Position of an instant, expressed using xsd:dateTimeStamp
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: inXSDDateTimeStamp

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship stating the timestamp of an entity (e.g. a measurement).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has timestamp

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship defining the value of a certain property, e.g., energy or power. Note that, even if numeric values are expected to enable reasoning, measurement values could use other datatypes.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has value

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between the confidence (s4auto:Confidence) and its value, which can be a discrete value (+/- 5 cm/s) or a level (e.g. 95 %)
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasConfidenceValue

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to define the X coordinate of a relative position
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasCoordinateX

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to define the Y coordinate of a relative position
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasCoordinateY

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to define the Z coordinate of a relative position
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasCoordinateY

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to define that a parking spot can have a description name
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasDescriptionName

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express that, during the forming state, a vehicle member of a platoon is given an estimated time for joining
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasEstimatedJoiningTime

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relationship to define the value of an indentifier
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasIDValue

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the max size of a platoon. Note that it is defined as a datatype property as this is a fixed/static value of the platoon that does not change over time. In contrast, the current size of the platoon is actually a measurement that may change over time and it is therefore defined as an object property (see s4auto:hasSize).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasMaxSize

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation to express the index of the vehicle in the platoon starting from zero (leader) up to N (trailing vehicle)
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasPlatoonIndex

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class represents the top-level feature type. This class is equivalent to GFI_Feature defined in ISO 19156:2011, and it is superclass of all feature types.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Feature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class represents the top-level geometry type. This class is equivalent to the UML class GM_Object defined in ISO 19107, and it is superclass of all geometry types.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Geometry

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class spatial-object represents everything that can have a spatial representation. It is superclass of feature and geometry.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SpatialObject

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A point, typically described using a coordinate system relative to Earth, such as WGS84.

Uniquely identified by lat/long/alt. i.e.
spaciallyIntersects(P1, P2) :- lat(P1, LAT), long(P1, LONG), alt(P1, ALT), lat(P2, LAT), long(P2, LONG), alt(P2, ALT).
sameThing(P1, P2) :- type(P1, Point), type(P2, Point), spaciallyIntersects(P1, P2).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Point

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Anything with spatial extent, i.e. size, shape, or position. e.g. people, places, bowling balls, as well as abstract areas like cubes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Spatial Thing

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal entity with zero extent or duration
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Instant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal entity with an extent or duration
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Interval

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal interval or instant.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TemporaryEntity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A device responsible for moving or controlling a mechanism or system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actuator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A tangible object designed to accomplish a particular task in households, common public buildings or offices. In order to accomplish this task, the device performs one or more functions. For example, a washing machine is designed to wash (task) and to accomplish this task it performs a start and stop function. Devices can be structured in categories (subclasses) that reflect the different domain in which a device is used, e.g., smart appliances domain (subclass FunctionRelated) vs. building domain (subclass BuildingRelated) vs. smart grid domain (subclass EnergyRelated). New categories can be defined,if needed, to reflect other differences, for example different points of view, such as the point of view of the device's user vs. the point of view of the device's manufacturer. We propose a list of devices that are relevant for the purpose of SAREF, but this list can be extended.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Device

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A feature of interest represents any real world entity from which a property is measured.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: FeatureOfInterest

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents the measured value made over a property. It is also linked to the unit of measure in which the value is expressed and the timestamp of the measurement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Measurement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Anything that can be sensed, measured or controlled by a device (measured by a sensor, controlled by an actuator) .
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Property

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A device that detects and responds to events or changes in the physical environment such as light, motion, or temperature changes. A device that has category saref:Sensor and performs a saref:SensingFunction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The state in which a device can be found, e.g, ON/OFF/STANDBY, or ONLINE/OFFLINE. We propose here a list of states that are relevant for the purpose of SAREF, but this list can be extended.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: State

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The unit of measure is a standard for measurement of a quantity, such as a Property. For example, Power is a property and Watt is a unit of power that represents a definite predetermined power: when we say 10 Watt, we actually mean 10 times the definite predetermined power called "watt". Our definition is based on the definition of unit of measure in the Ontology of units of Measure (OM). We propose here a list of some units of measure that are relevant for the purpose of SAREF, but this list can be extended, also using some other ontologies rather than the Ontology of units of Measure (OM).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: UnitOfMeasure

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The absolute poistion of an automotive object in terms of lat, long and lat
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AbsolutePosition

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of speed
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AbsoluteSpeed

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Acceleration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of confidence for acceleration measurements that represents the absolute accuracy of a reported vehicle acceleration value with a predefined confidence level (e.g. 95 %)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AccelerationConfidence

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A class to define common information related to an address. It is out of scope of SAREF4AUTO to define the details of such an address. It is instead recommended to reuse existing ontologies that specify how to model an address in terms of Street, Postal Code, City, Region, Country, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Address

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of heading
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AngularDirection

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Platoon
owl:Class.rdfs:label: assembling

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: At Drop Off Spot

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: At Pick Up Spot

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The level of automation a platoon of vehicles or a singular vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AutomationLevel

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The main objects of interest in the automotive domain.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AutomotiveObject

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BrakeCapacity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of public transport
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Bus

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of vehicle. Example of a car is a passenger car
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Car

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: unit of measure of size
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cardinality unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Spot or for Parking Vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: charging

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Spot
owl:Class.rdfs:label: closed

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Every measurement in the automotive domain is an estimated measurement coming from the aggregation of several measurements from different sensor or devices taken at the same time or at consecutive times very close to each other. Therefore, a confidence is always associated to each mesurement to indicate that it has not 100% accuracy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Confidence

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A critical object located on the road. Critical objects are small object, medium object, large object
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CriticalObject

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Platoon or for a Vehicle in a Platoon
owl:Class.rdfs:label: disengaging

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Driving To Parking Spot

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Driving To Pick Up Spot

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type pf parking spot
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ElectricChargingParkingSpot

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An electronic control unit (ECU) is any embedded system in automotive electronics that monitors and controls one or more of the electrical systems or subsystems in a vehicle. The ECU provides measurements about relevant properties of the vehicle, such as speed, acceleration, position, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ElectronicControlUnit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The final destination of a vehicle or a platoon, or the final point of a route
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EndPoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for a Vehicle in a Platoon
owl:Class.rdfs:label: engaging

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for a Vehicle in a Platoon
owl:Class.rdfs:label: forming

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Spot
owl:Class.rdfs:label: free

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Heading

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of truck
owl:Class.rdfs:label: HeavyTruck

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Height

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: unit of measure of height
owl:Class.rdfs:label: height unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A class used to identify 1) a vehicle (station) during data exchange with other devices/stations 2) a platoon during data exchange with other devices/stations, 3) a parking spot within a parking area during data exchange with other devices/stations. In all cases, this identifier may be a pseudonym. It may change over space and/or over time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of Critical Object
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Large Object

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of acceleration
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Lateral Acceleration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain

In a platoon, a property to express that a platoon has a size. This size is defined as 1) the total number of vehicles currently in the platoon (see s4auto:Size class); or 2) Length of the platoon (sum of all vehicles' length + inter-vehicle distance)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Length

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: unit of measure of lenght
owl:Class.rdfs:label: length unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of truck
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LightTruck

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of acceleration
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LongitudinalAcceleration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of Critical Object
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Medium Object

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain. Relevant types of movement are: Static (position only), moving in same direction (speed, acceleration), moving in reverse direction (speed acceleration), crossing (speed, acceleration, direction)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Movement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The relevant types of events are trafficCondition, accident, roadworks, impassability, adverseWeatherCondition-Adhesion, aquaplannning, hazardousLocation-SurfaceCondition, hazardousLocation-ObstacleOnTheRoad, hazardousLocation-AnimalOnTheRoad, humanPresenceOnTheRoad, wrongWayDriving, rescueAndRecoveryWorkInProgress, adverseWeatherCondition-ExtremeWeatherCondition, adverseWeatherCondition-Visibility, adverseWeatherCondition-Precipitation, slowVehicle, dangerousEndOfQueue, vehicleBreakdown, postCrash, humanProblem, stationaryVehicle, emergencyVehicleApproaching, hazardousLocation-DangerousCurve, collisionRisk, signalViolation, dangerousSituation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: NotifiedEvent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Property of interest. Flow of vehicle or people in a specific point
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Flow

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: GIS shapefile of TAZ system and georeferences of centroids and connectors
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TAZ_system_data

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Historical data
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Number_of_passengers

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: To indicate the number of an entity in a fraction of time. Number per second
owl:Class.rdfs:label: flow unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: To indicate when each datum is caputred
owl:Class.rdfs:label: timestamp

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: GIS shapefile of study area
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Open_street_map_data

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Spot
owl:Class.rdfs:label: occupied

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: VRU Profile 1 users, for example: adult, child, elderly person, pram, animal, blind person guided by a dog, rider off its bike
owl:Class.rdfs:label: P1 Pedestrian

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: VRU Profile 2 users, for example: user of bicycle, wheelchair, skater, scooter, Segway, or a mounted horse rider
owl:Class.rdfs:label: P2 Bicyclist

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: VRU Profile 3 users are Motorcyclists, which are equipped with engines that allow them to move on the road. It includes users (driver and passengers, e.g. children and animals) of Powered Two Wheelers (PTW) such as mopeds (motorized scooters), motorcycles or side-cars.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: P3 Motorcyclist

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: VRU Profile 4 animals presenting a safety risk to other road users, for example : dogs, wild animals, horses, cows, sheep, kangaroos, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: P4 Animal

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: parked

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: parking

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A location that is designated for parking. A parking spot has a geometry defining the parking area boundaries and its centre point
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ParkingSpot

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: the position of aparking spot (its centre point) in terms of lat, long and alt
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ParkingSpotPoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A parking spot has a state. Possible values for parking spot state are Free, occupied, reserved, closed, charging
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ParkingSpotState

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A vehicle can be found at different states (or parking phases) during parking . Possible values for parking state (or parking phase) of a vehicle are: At drop-off spot, at pick-up spot, driving to parking spot, driving to pick up spot, parking, parked, charging.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ParkingVehicleState

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of car
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PassengerCar

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A state of the vehicle related to its environment
owl:Class.rdfs:label: perception state

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A personal device is a nomadic device used by a pedestrian or the rider of a two-wheeler. A personal device in modelled as a different type of automotive object, as it normally does not have access to the vehicle CAN bus.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PersonalDevice

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A group of vehicles automatically following each other at a relatively close distance
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Platoon

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A level of automation is defined for a vehicle that it is platooning. For example, in the ENSEMBLE project there are three levels of platoon automation defined: Level A, Level B, Level C. Level C represents the highest level of automation for platooning in terms of longitudinal and lateral control, shortest time gap supported, wider range of situations handled and support for merging of entire platoons.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PlatoonAutomationLevel

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A vehicle member of a platoon has a platoon position that is defined as the index of the vehicle in the platoon starting from zero (leader) up to N (trailing vehicle).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PlatoonPosition

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: In platoon a vehicle can assume roles such as: unknown, leader, follower, ready-for-leading, trailing, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PlatoonRole

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The state of a platoon. Examples of states for a platoon are: unknown, standalone, assembling, platooning, disengaging, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PlatoonState

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Examples of states for a vehicle in a platoon are: unknown, standalone, engaging, platooning, disengaging, searching, forming.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PlatoonVehicleState

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Platoon or for a Vehicle in a Platoon
owl:Class.rdfs:label: platooning

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A geo point in SAREF4AUTO
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Point

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The position of an entity in the automotive domain
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Position

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of confidence that represents horizontal position accuracy in a shape of ellipse with a predefined confidence level (e.g. 95 %). The centre of the ellipse shape corresponds to the reference position point for which the position accuracy is evaluated.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PositionConfidenceEllipse

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type pf parking spot
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RegularParkingSpot

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It represents the relative position of a vehicle (e.g., a car is x,y,z in front of another car)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RelativePosition

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of speed
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RelativeSpeed

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the estimated location where the vehicle member joins the platoon. It is expressed in global coordinates (lat, long, alt), e.g. according to WGS 84.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RendezvousLocation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Parking Spot
owl:Class.rdfs:label: reserved

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An entity present on the road in the neighbouring area of a vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RoadEntity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Road side sensors measure properties (such as speed, position, dimension, direction, etc.) of road objects. Types of relevant road objects are Pedestrian, vehicles, obstacles, traffic signs, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RoadObject

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Devices deployed along the road that produce signals based on road side sensor data measurements. Types of road side actuators that are relevant are devices such as traffic light controllers changing from red to green based on detected vehicles.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RoadSideActuator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A road side equipment can be either a simple data relay between vehicles and infrastructure or between the vehicles themselves, or it can run applications. It is usually high mounted in existing equipment, such as a street light, city traffic light, VMS or highway sign, or has its own pole.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RoadSideEquipment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sensors such as cameras, radars that are deployed along the road (e.g. at intersections and at poles along a highway). Road side sensors perform measurements, such as speed, position (relative or absolute), dimension, direction, etc. of road objects.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RoadSideSensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Position with respect to road topology (e.g. road, segment or lane) and lane characteristics (highway lane, road lane, bicycle lane, pavement, off-road).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Road Topology Position

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The role that can be assumed by a vehicle or a platoon
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Role

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The route of a vehicle or of a platoon. The route of a platoon is defined as the route of the current vehicle leader in the platoon that other follower vehicles (partially) share
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Route

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The intermediate points of a route
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RoutePoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for a Vehicle in a Platoon
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Searching

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain. It defines the overall shape of an entity: i.e., Sphere, Torus, Cylinder, Cone, Ellipsoid, Cube, Cuboid, Pyramid, Prism, Multiple shapes
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Shape

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain. A platoon has a size. Tis size is defined as 1) the total number of vehicles currently in the platoon; or 2) Length of the platoon (sum of all vehicles' length + inter-vehicle distance)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Size

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of Critical Object
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Small Object

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type pf parking spot. Parking spot reserved for special permits (authorities, disabled, blue Zone, resident ...)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SpecialPermitParkingSpot

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Speed

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of confidence for speed measurements that represents absolute accuracy of a speed value in cm/s
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SpeedConfidence

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: unit of measure of speed
owl:Class.rdfs:label: speed unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Platoon or for a Vehicle in a Platoon
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standalone

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The origin of a route
owl:Class.rdfs:label: StartPoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A class dedicated to describe the relevant states in the automotive domain
owl:Class.rdfs:label: State

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of identifier for vehicles and platoons, as defined in ETSI TS 102 894-2.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: StationID

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A device that automatically operates coloured lights, typically red, amber, and green, for controlling traffic at road junctions, pedestrian crossings, and roundabouts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TrafficLight

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A traffic centre provides services to road users: exploiting data for road traffic management, providing information about mobility zones, operational management of the road infrastructure, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TrafficManagementCentre

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of public transport
owl:Class.rdfs:label: tram

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of vehicle. Example of trucks are heavy trucks or light trucks.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Truck

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of vehicle. This class involves all sorts of two wheelers, from motorcycles to bicycles and (e-)scooters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TwoWheeler

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A universally unique identifier (UUID) is a 128-bit number used to identify items and is also known as: globally unique identifier (GUID). In its canonical textual representation, the sixteen octets of a UUID are represented as 32 hexadecimal (base 16) digits, displayed in five groups separated by hyphens, in the form 8-4-4-4-12 for a total of 36 characters (32 alphanumeric characters and four hyphens). UUID are documented in ISO/IEC 11578:1996 "Information technology – Open Systems Interconnection – Remote Procedure Call (RPC)" and in ITU-T Rec. X.667 ISO/IEC 9834-8:2005.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: UUID

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A vehicle is the main object of interest in the automotive domain. Example of types of vehicles are car, truck, public transport and two-wheeler. See ETSI TS 102 894-2 spec for full list of vehicles, which are type of "stations". See also the SENSORIS data model for possible type of vehicles. The main IoT device considered in the vehicle is the ECU (part of the vehicle on board equipment, or OBE), see s4auto:ElectronicControlUnit class.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Vehicle

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: According to SAE J3016, there are five levels of automation for a vehicle: - Level 0: No Driving Automation. - Level 1: Driver assistance. - Level 2: Partial driving automation. - Level 3: Conditional driving automation. - Level 4: High driving automation. - Level 5: Full Driving automation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: VehicleAutomationLevel

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The vehicle environment is made of entities which are present on the road in the area around the vehicle
owl:Class.rdfs:label: VehicleEnvironment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The role the vehicle plays in traffic. If not specified, it is assumed that it takes a default value. Otherwise, possible values to be specified are: publicTransport, specialTransport, dangerousGoods, roadWork, rescue, emergency, safetyCar, agriculture, commercial, military, roadOperator, taxi.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: VehicleRole

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Non-motorized road users as well as users of VRU vehicles (L class of vehicles, for example mopeds or motorcycles, etc.) participating to the road traffic
owl:Class.rdfs:label: VulnerableRoadUser

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Weight

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Property of interest for the automotive domain
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Width

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: unit of measure of width
owl:Class.rdfs:label: width unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of heading
owl:Class.rdfs:label: YawRate

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of systems, i.e., systems virtually isolated from the environment, whose behaviour and interactions with the environment are modeled. Systems can be connected to other systems. Connected systems interact in some ways. Systems can also have subsystems. Properties of subsystems somehow contribute to the properties of the supersystem
owl:Class.rdfs:label: System

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A type of vehicle. Example of public transport is a bus or a tram
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: PublicTransport
publicTransport

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A type of state for Platoon or for a Vehicle in a Platoon
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: unknown
